# List-page CRUD

Canonical pattern for feature list pages (members, departments, locations). Do not invent parallel dialog stacks or skip RBAC UI gates.

## Shape

1. Load list via `useError().run(listX())`; keep a `load()` helper for post-mutation refresh
2. Gate write UI with `can(me.role, Actions.<feature>.write)` from `@/features/auth/permissions`
3. `DynamicTable` gets `toolbarActions` (Create) and `rowActions` (Edit / Delete)
4. Create/Edit → `openModal({ type: "form", … })` + dirty bridge + `run` + `applyServerErrors` + toast + `closeModal` + `load()`
5. Delete → `confirm({ variant: "destructive" })` → `run(deleteX(id))` → toast + `load()`
6. Empty state still shows Create when `canWrite` (not a dead end)
7. Show “Loading…” until first fetch settles (`loaded` flag). Lists are full arrays — DynamicTable pages/filters client-side only
8. Do not add `[id]` detail routes or orphan `getX(id)` unless the task asks for them

```ts
const canWrite = me ? can(me.role, Actions.users.write) : false

await authorize(Actions.users.write) // server actions only
```

## Imports

| Need | From |
|------|------|
| Table | `@/components/shared/table/dynamic-table` |
| Modals | `@/components/shared/modals` → `useModal` |
| Errors | `@/features/errors` → `useError` |
| RBAC UI | `@/features/auth/permissions` → `Actions`, `can` |
| Auth me | `@/features/auth/hooks/use-auth` |

Never import `@/features/auth/session` or `@/features/errors/server` from list pages.

## App route

Thin wrapper under `src/app/(app)/…/page.tsx` that mounts the feature `*ListPageComponent` (full-bleed `table-shell` layout as in team/members).

See `.docs/components/list-pages.md` and mirror `src/features/users/components/pages/userlist-page-component.tsx`.
